		<div id="comment_body_64642784">Coding is a shop class, an elective, not a core class. Basically it for the kids who are curious, to discover if they have any persistent genuine interest or aptitude. Should kids be encouraged, sure, as much as they are encouraged to take wood shop. Later in life wood shop might let them fix some minor things around the house, and a coding class might let them write a python program that does something useful for them on their computer.<br> <br>

And like shop classes, if a kid developed an interest in that basic</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64642784">

</div>
