		<div id="comment_body_64642484"><p>Changing a tyre is as easy as mowing the lawn. Kids don't need to be taught that sort of thing in school. General logical problem solving skills are, on the other hand, widely applicable. Training your brain to think logically and to problem solve is good for you brain in the way that working out in the gym is good for your body: even if when your workout is done, all the weights are left where you found them, and no actual work is done, your body is healthier for the effort.</p></div>
