	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64642550"><p>Exactly this. Some kids, namely those interested in it, should learn whatever they fancy and coding can be among that. But most people can never be good at coding. Accept it and move on. Coding well is hard. Coding badly is expensive, sometimes exceptionally expensive. And, even if the general public does not realize this, coding using AI is actually harder. AI code adds hard to spot mistakes and may well solve the wrong problem. To spot that, you need to be able to code _better_ than you would have to be a<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
