		<div id="comment_body_64642586"><p>I'd advise that the basic design approach to a program is highly applicable to many life problems. You need to define the end goals clearly and consider the steps needed to get there. The steps are broken into manageable parts that may need to be followed in a specific order. You know what each part is supposed to do and can test it to see if it's working properly.</p><p>This is directly applicable to dieting, budgeting, and any other long-term goals.</p></div>
