	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64642388"><p><div class="quote"><p>95%+ of adult humans never actually utilize math skills beyond the 4th grade</p></div><p>This is not an argument against teaching math, because the same argument applies to nearly everything else school teaches beyond basic writing skills. Nobody uses middle school science* "barium burns light green in a flame", "the Mohorovicic discontinuity lies 5-10km / 3-6 mi below ocean floor". The purpose of school is not to teach practical trades, it is to make you an educated person who knows the how and why. You won't learn "to fix your car", but you might learn how engines work. You won't learn "how to do your taxes", but you might learn basics of economics and accounting. It is good for the young to learn basics of programming, which is excellent at forming logical minds (a quality needed in many trades).</p></div>
	</div>

