	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64642584"><p>Indeed. Compilers are zero-error tools (not quite in reality, but that is the goal). LLMs are not zero-error tools and cannot ever be. Hence they have no place in a workflow that is aimed at generating working (correct, reliable, secure) code.</p><p>Also note that this "metaprogramming" idea has been tried time and again. It has always failed. Sometimes it produces additional languages that stick around.</p></div>
	</div>

