	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64642256"><p>I think coding should be part of a basic curriculum - but you don't need to learn anything modern or fancy, just the concept of ordered groups of instructions passing values to each other and resulting in a desired outcome.  It doesn't matter if you never sit in front of a computer, learning how to dissect a problem into component parts so you can solve it is a generally useful life skill.</p><p>Then again, I'm crazy, I think you should have basic instruction in statistics and probability as well.  And civics.  We put too many kids out into the world without the ability to understand it, which makes them fearful, angry, and helpless and from there vulnerable to being manipulated and exploited.</p></div>
	</div>

